### Classification of Criminal Courts
According to the **Code of Criminal Procedure (1973)** in every state there shall be criminal courts of the following classes:
(i) **Courts of Sessions**;
(ii) **Judicial Magistrates of the First Class** and in any Metropolitan area **Metropolitan Magistrates**;
(iii) **Judicial Magistrates of the Second Class**;
(iv) **Executive Magistrates**.

